# REVIEW.md — Semantic Lint Rules

> These are the things deterministic tests CAN'T catch. They require judgment. Each rule is checked by a dedicated review agent during coherency rounds.

## How it works

- **Deterministic tests** (vitest, pytest, etc.) run every Reflect. They catch exact failures.
- **Semantic reviews** (this file) run every coherency round. They catch quality, intent, and UX issues that tests can't express.
- During coherency, 3-8 review agents are launched based on the complexity of this file. Each agent owns a section and reviews ALL changes since the last coherency round.

## Review Scope

Each review agent runs: `git diff HEAD~{commits_since_last_coherency} -- .` to get all changes, then evaluates them against its assigned rules.

