## Rules

{{PROJECT-SPECIFIC SEMANTIC RULES}}

### Template examples (customize for your project):

### Interpretability
Every decision the system flags (low, high, anomalous, etc.) MUST be interpretable:
- What formula/threshold was used?
- What data went into the calculation?
- Why was this flagged and not that?
- A user should be able to trace any flag back to its source data.

### Feedback Surface
Every user-facing judgment MUST have a feedback mechanism:
- A "this is incorrect" button, flag, or channel
- Feedback must be captured with context (what was shown, what the user expected)
- Feedback feeds back into the system (explorer findings, data corrections, threshold adjustments)

### Progressive Disclosure
Don't dump all data at once:
- Summary first (1-3 key numbers)
- Drill-down available on demand
- Suggestion chips for next actions

### Professional Tone
No emoji, no casual language in production outputs. Domain-appropriate terminology. Data disclaimers where applicable.

### No Black Boxes
If the system makes a recommendation, it must show its work. No "trust me" verdicts. Every output should answer: "why this number?" and "where did this data come from?"
